article.headline: Texas State 65, Alcorn State 49
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Zach Allison had 18 points and 14 rebounds to lead Texas State past struggling Alcorn State 65-49 on Saturday. Anthony Dill had 12 points and 10 rebounds and Josh Naylor added 11 points for Texas State (2-1), which took control with a 16-1 run in the first half. DeAndre Jones had 12 points and Delvin Thompson added 10 for Alcorn State, which is 0-5 for the second straight year. The Braves did not manage their first points of the second half until Almaad Jackson knocked down a jumper with 16:37 remaining. Trailing by 18 points, Alcorn State cut the lead to 11 with 14:16 left with John Chandler and Jones scoring the next seven points. That was as close as Alcorn State would get. Texas State responded with a 12-4 run. The Braves made just 21 percent (16-of-55) of their attempts from the field.
